what are pure Cmponent?
***********************************************
A Pure Component in React is a special type of component that only re-renders when its state or props change.
 It helps optimize performance by preventing unnecessary re-renders

Using React.memo() for Functional Components
üîπ React.memo() wraps the functional component and prevents re-rendering unless props change.
*********
import React from "react";

const MyFunctionalComponent = React.memo(({ name }) => {
  console.log("Rendered!");
  return <h1>Hello, {name}!</h1>;
});

export default MyFunctionalComponent;
*********
import React, { useState } from "react";
import MyFunctionalComponent from "./MyFunctionalComponent";

const App = () => {
  const [count, setCount] = useState(0);

  return (
    <div>
      <MyFunctionalComponent name="Ashish" />
      <h2>Count: {count}</h2>
      <button onClick={() => setCount(count + 1)}>Increment</button>
    </div>
  );
};

export default App;
*************************************
When to Use Pure Components?
‚úÖ When dealing with components that receive the same props most of the time
‚úÖ When optimizing performance in large applications
‚úÖ When working with stateless functional components (use React.memo)
